        <content>
          <p>CHAPTER 2.  OF THE CAPACITY NECESSARY FOR DISPOSING
AND RECEIVING BY DONATION INTER VIVOS
OR MORTIS CAUSA
Art. 1470.  Persons capable of giving or receiving
All persons have capacity to make and receive donations inter vivos and mortis causa, except as expressly provided by law.</p>
        </content>
